1.	Actor:
•	Student: The students interact with the system to view dashboard, view assignments, and receive reminders.
•	Lecturer: The lecturer uses the system to manage assignments.

2.	Student Use Cases:
•	Register
Students must first register an account in the system by providing the required information.
•	Log in
After registering, students can log into the system to access assignment tracking features. The registration process is included as part of accessing the system for new users.
•	View Dashboard
Students can access dashboard that summarizes their assignment information such as upcoming deadlines and submitted assignments.
•	View Assignments
Students can view a list of assignments provided by the lecturer.
•	View Details (Included Use Case)
When students selected an assignment, they can view more detailed information such as instructions, due date, and requirements.
•	Submit Assignments (Extended Use Case)
After viewing assignment details, students can submit their completed assignments through the system.
•	Receive Reminder
Students receive reminders or notifications about upcoming assignments deadlines to help them submit their work on time.


3.	Lecturer Use Cases:
•	Log in
Lecturers must log into the system to manage assignments.
•	Manage Assignments
This is the main function for lecturers. They can control all assignment-related tasks.
The following use cases extend the Manage Assignments function:
-	Create Assignment – Lecturers can create new assignments and provide instructions and deadline.
-	Edit Assignment – Lecturers can update assignment details if necessary.
-	Delete Assignment – Lecturers can remove assignments from the system.
-	View Submissions – Lecturers can review assignments submitted by students.

4.	Relationships in the Diagram
•	<<include>> Relationship
The <<include>> relationship indicates that a use case must always perform another use case as a part of its process.
Example:
-	View Assignments includes View Details

•	<<extend>> Relationship
The <<extend>> relationship represents optional or additional functionality that extend a main use case.
Example:
-	Create, Edit, Delete Assignment, and View Submissions extend Manage Assignments.


